Pirates are always going to win this fight. It's much easier to loan disks to a friend and let them do an install than to backup your copy already on disk, and then give them that. All anyone needs to do is find the part of the code that does the quiz, and insert a JMP instruction to skip it.
Pirates who see copy protection as a challenge love breaking them, and no amount of copy protection will stop them. Check out Xicor's new goodie in the April 12th edition of EETimes X88C64 - an 8k * 8 E2PROM with built in latch AND bootloader setup.
A single chip micro and a crystal will do the job reliably and easily. Embed the whole thing in a foam insulated blanket, power it from a solar cell. If you don't want to try thermal management, contact someone like ICL and have them cut you a special low temperature crystal.
