It sounds like the radio equipment is actually not shut completely off - but just goes to a standby situation. The voltage can only be sucked down so far instantaneously. A transmitter is not going to be affecting house power. If surges are occurring there, it is due to another cause - not a transmitter.
Use a quartz crystal and divide its frequency by 2 40 times or something like that. In Texas (Corpus Christi at least) if you pick up the phone and dial 890 the phone company will read the number of the phone you are on back to you. The number to dial is 211 for the same result. If you're going to want those big capacitors you found to fire the current drain on the solenoid on the High High. High.
